{"title":"2026 Bespoked UK Selects 03: BabyLdn, Boyd Wheels, Julius Randonneur, Medusa, Quirk, Stout, Tomo – John Watson","link":"https://theradavist.com/2026-bespoked-uk-03","date":1777359624000,"content":"<p><em>John and Cari are at the <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/2026-bespoked-uk\" target=\"_blank\">2026 Bespoked UK</a> show in London and are elated to share their third selection of bikes from the event with you, featuring <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/babyldn\" target=\"_blank\">BabyLdn</a>, <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/boyd-wheels\" target=\"_blank\">Boyd Wheels</a>, Julius Randonneur, <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/medusa-cycles\" target=\"_blank\">Medusa</a>, <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/quirk-cycles\" target=\"_blank\">Quirk</a>, <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/stout-cycles\" target=\"_blank\">Stout</a>, and <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/tomo-bikes\" target=\"_blank\">Tomo</a>…</em><br />\n<span></span></p>\n<p><strong>The Radavist thanks <a href=\"https://www.brooksengland.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Brooks England</a> and <a href=\"https://www.schwalbe.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Schwalbe</a> for sponsoring our <a href=\"https://www.bespoked.cc/uk-2026\" target=\"_blank\">2026 Bespoked UK</a> coverage and our independent Reportage!</strong></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-29.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-29.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-29.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-29.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.babyldn.com/\" target=\"_blank\">BabyLdn</a> x <a href=\"https://www.stayercycles.com/product/staytb-frame/\" target=\"_blank\">Stayer Cycles StayTB</a></h3>\n<p>Marlon from the London-based shop BabyLdn debuted his shop’s special Stayer Cycles StayTB build at the 2026 Bespoked UK. The StayTB is Stayer Cycles’ 650b homage to vintage mountain bikes, just updated for a larger wheel diameter and disc brakes. You can also build these bikes with a 26+ wheelset, as Marlon did with his size small.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-1.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>These bikes are super smart and feature a modular dropout system, which allows for QR or thru-axle, so you don’t have to ditch your existing disc wheels to make them work.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-38.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-38.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-38.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-38.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-34.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-34.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-34.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-34.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-26.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-26.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-26.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-26.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>This bike is LOUD. So loud. Loud like a block party in the summer. Marlon commented that he’d normally prefer a more earthtone drab paint, but that the fluoro was growing on him. Even with the ostentatious bright paint – which I purposely photographed in the shade to catch its “pop” – Marlon’s build is sublimely exquisite, leaning on a mix of bintage and modern components.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-22.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-22.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-22.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-22.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-19.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-19.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-19.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-19.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-17.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-17.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-17.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-17.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>A rapid rise XTR mech, vintage front rack he got from a swap, King headset, Dura Ace friction barcons, Velo Orange stem with Rune handlebars, Growtac discs, Campagnolo levers, and a Campagnolo triple crankset dial in the style of the build. The bags are from Manivelle, and the front panniers are from Brooks.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-31.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-31.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-31.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Babyldn-Bikes-Stayer-31.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Marlon’s usually not a fan of drop bars, but he commented that the Rune bars were so wide that they felt great. The BabyLdn StayTB is available through BabyLdn bikes, where you can have Marlon make you one to suit your needs.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Wizard-Works-8.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Wizard-Works-8.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Wizard-Works-8.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Wizard-Works-8.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>One thing that you lose out on with drops is the ability to run the new <a href=\"https://www.babyldn.com/merch-1/p/esi-limited-custom-tenneessee-williams-grips-collab\" target=\"_blank\">BabyLdn ESI grips</a>, which come in either “snake” or “croc,” in three color options. I had to buy two pairs! The <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/tennessee_makes/\" target=\"_blank\">Tennessee Williams</a> animal designs are so good.</p>\n<p>Excellent build. 10/10, no notes.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/babyldn.bikes/\" target=\"_blank\">@BabyLdn</a> <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/stayercycles/\" target=\"_blank\">@StayerCycles</a></h3>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-2.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-2.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.boydcycling.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Boyd 32er Kanuga Wheels</a></h3>\n<p>Greenville, South Carolina’s Boyd Wheels debuted its Kanuga <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/32er\" target=\"_blank\">32er</a> silver wheels aboard a beautiful Singular Albatross build at the 2026 Bespoked UK show. With 32er wheels dominating <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/2026-sea-otter-classic\" target=\"_blank\">our Sea Otter Classic coverage</a>, it should come as no surprise that I documented a few big wheel builds at Bespoked as well.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-6.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-6.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-6.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-6.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-8.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-8.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-8.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-8.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>These silver hoops feature a 30 mm internal width with a massive 37 mm external width, which utilizes what Boyd calls a “reverse hook” to improve impact performance. Boyd claims that the Kanuga’s shallow rim profile enhances perceived compliance on the 32er platform, while a generous 4 mm spoke offset helps keep the spoke balance even. The rim’s profile features a flattened section. The Kanuga is Boyd’s all-mountain wheel, and the brand is hoping to make a splash with it in the new diameter, where durability is for sure a concern.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-1.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Boyd UK’s Rory Hitchens built up this Singular Albatross to display the new wheel diameter and cranked it to eleven on the build, even modifying the Restrap rack to clear the additional wheel height. While we’re sure it’s safe, we 100% believe this will void the warranty, so don’t try it at home!</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-3.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-3.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-3.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-3.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-7.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-7.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-7.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-7.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-18.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-18.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-18.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Singular-Albatross-18.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Other silver bits and bobs include the SRAM 1987 groupset, Hex Components parts, and PNW Loam cockpit.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/boydcycling/\" target=\"_blank\">@BoydCycling</a> <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/singularcycles/\" target=\"_blank\">@SingularCycles</a></h3>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-1.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Julius Randonneur</h3>\n<p>Whoa, baby! Julius lives on the edge of the Black Forest in Germany and was one of the few tube-to-tube lugged builders in attendance at Bespoked this year. Technically, he’s not a builder, in the business sense. He just wanted to make a custom bike for himself, using the guiding history of Rene Herse and other constructeurs, and boy, did he deliver.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-21.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-21.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-21.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-21.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-6.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-6.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-6.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-6.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-37.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-37.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-37.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-37.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Let’s begin with the most obvious French constructeur bit, a Rene Herse stem. Julius chose it to be the start of the build. It established a circle motif with the bike, as the cable stop passes through the face of the stem, giving it a circle on its profile. The steerer features a dynamo on/off switch, and there’s a decaleur for a rando bag.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-27.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-27.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-27.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-27.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-26.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-26.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-26.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-26.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Carrying over the circle motif is another homage to a constructeur, <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/charlie-cunningham\" target=\"_blank\">Charlie Cunningham</a>. Julius made his own FASP, or a fixed-angle seat post, similar to what the mountain bike pioneer designed for his custom aluminum bikes <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/charlie-cunningham\" target=\"_blank\">we’ve featured extensively here</a>. I must say, seeing a FASP in the UK was very exciting for me.</p>\n<p><em>Julius requested a link to <a href=\"https://www.gofundme.com/f/charlie-cunningham-medical-and-rehab\" target=\"_blank\">Charlie’s GoFundMe</a> to be added here, too. </em></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-36.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-36.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-36.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-36.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-34.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-34.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-34.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-34.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-31.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-31.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-31.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-31.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>While the two previously described components were inspired by some of cycling’s greatest constructeurs, Julius offered his own design for his Dura-Ace shifter. He carefully constructed this shifter from steel and actually brazed it to the stem/bar clamp band with a careful dollop of brass. Initially, he was worried the mount might break off, but after thousands of kilometers, it’s stayed intact.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-19.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-19.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-19.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-19.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-18.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-18.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-18.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-18.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Two legendary German component manufacturers were used for the hubs, SON and Tune, which is only a few kilometers from Julius’ home and shop in the Black Forest.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-29.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-29.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-29.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-29.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-28.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-28.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-28.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-28.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-24.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-24.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-24.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-24.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Moving onto the frame, where the details and careful, attentive eye for detailing continue. Julius stuck to traditional-diameter tubing, assembling the bike from Kaisei Superlight tubing and fork blades. The lugs came from all over. Llewelyn dropouts were modified by carefully drilling the hood out to accept the 10 mm seat stays, and a Henry James lug was used on the downtube/headtube.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-5.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-5.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-5.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-5.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-2.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-2.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The entire frame was nickel-plated, giving it a soft, semi-gloss sheen that absolutely loved being photographed in my photo setup.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-20.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-20.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-20.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Julius-Randonneur-20.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Bikes like this feel effortlessly classy, and that’s because of the amount of effort put into creating them. Before I could talk to him more, he had packed up and headed back home to Germany. This neo-retro build kit on such a classically-inspired frame feels like a rarity at modern bike shows. These bikes take a real concerted effort to document, spotting all the details and sopping them up with my lens. Is it special to me because it’s rare? Or is it rare because it’s special?</p>\n<p>Thank you, Julius.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/145604230@N07/\" target=\"_blank\">Follow Julius on Flickr</a></h3>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-1.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.medusa-cycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Medusa 29+ Touring Bike</a></h3>\n<p>Manchester-based Medusa returned to the Bespoked show with some stunning bikes. Pete Skelton’s work always impresses. This year, he won “Best in Show” for a bike he built for his girlfriend, Annie. But the bike that caught my eye was this 29+ tourer. Pete built this after his beloved Surly Long Haul trucker shook him to pieces from the rough roads during a bike tour in India. Seeking more comfort, he went with a plumper tire.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-28.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-28.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-28.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-28.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-27.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-27.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-27.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-27.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-7.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-7.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-7.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-7.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Wanting a triple crankset with a wide range rear mech for all the gear inches, he decided to go with an elevated chainstay to help optimize the boost spacing. Another move he had to make was to move the seat tube 3 mm outboard on the drive side to make shifting with the front mech possible. An integrated front rack that doubles as a simple truss fork ups the ante on an already very visually engaging bike.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-23.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-23.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-23.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-23.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-22.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-22.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-22.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-22.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Later, while touring through Turkey, he was chased by dozens of <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/search/Kangal\" target=\"_blank\">Kangals</a> while riding through the <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/turkish-highland-bike-touring\" target=\"_blank\">Anatolian steppe</a>, which inspired the Turkish eye on his elevated chainstay bridge. On the fork crown, Pete silver soldered his signature Medusa coin.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-37.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-37.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-37.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Medusa-37.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-91.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-91.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-91.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-91.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Pete’s been building for about five years now, and I’m always impressed with what he brings to Bespoked each year. This bike is sculptural and wonderful, just like the new haircut that Petor gave him on the Bespoked show floor!</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/medusa.cycles/\" target=\"_blank\">@MedusaCycles</a></h3>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-1.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.quirkcycles.com/durmitor\" target=\"_blank\">Quirk Cycles Durmitor Disc Road</a></h3>\n<p>London-based Quirk Cycles brought quite the selection this year, with a build from each of its batch production models. Since I’d linked up with <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/quirk-cycles-kegety-production-gravel-bike\" target=\"_blank\">Rob last year at the Forest Fondo and shot his Kegety model</a>, I wanted to affix my lens to the Durmitor road bike for the 2026 Bespoked UK show. Using 3D sintered stainless components, designed in collaboration with Sturdy Cycles, the Durmitor carries over the same visual language as the Kegety.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-5.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-5.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-5.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-5.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-10.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-10.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-10.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-10.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-14.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-14.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-14.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-14.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The Durmitor features a beautiful seat cluster with a hidden wedge bolt, dropouts, an integrated cockpit using the Enve system, and a 3D printed logo on the head tube.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-19.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-19.jpg?w=200&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-19.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-18.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-18.jpg?w=200&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-18.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-16.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-16.jpg?w=200&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-16.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-17.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-17.jpg?w=200&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-17.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>There are all sorts of little easter eggs found throughout the frame, along with a stunning set of Enve’s silver hubs.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-13.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-13.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-13.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Quirk-13.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Keep it sexy, Rob!</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/quirkcycles/\" target=\"_blank\">@QuirkCycles</a></h3>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-5.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-5.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-5.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-5.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.stoutcycles.co.uk/blog/32-wheel-yeah-or-nae\" target=\"_blank\">Stout Cycles Hrok 32er</a></h3>\n<p>Peebles, Scotland-based Stout Cycles brought along a very nice 32er hardtail that he “whipped up” for the show. Russell Stout is a very humble builder, and his downplaying the build a bit to me is a testament to that. For it being a last-minute build, equipped with lots of used parts, it’s one of my favorites from the show.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-11.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-11.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-11.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-11.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-10.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-10.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-10.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-10.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-12.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-12.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-12.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-12.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Russell works with Deda aluminum, and he does his own paint. But that doesn’t mean he’s too busy to design a chassis specifically for the new 32er platform. He immediately noted that the bike’s head tube, at 65º, was too slack for his taste. And that the rear end took some getting used to. And that he’s already broken one rear wheel.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-21.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-21.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-21.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-21.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-19.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-19.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-19.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-19.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>When I asked about the bike length penalty, he said, “It’s not too long – only 4 cm longer than my trail bike. But that’s also because I made the rear end very short.” He explained that the “bike rode very well on the steep sections of trail but was too cumbersome on anything else.” He still has some tweaks to make before he builds a customer one. The Stout 32er is still a work in progress.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-9.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-9.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-9.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-9.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-6.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-6.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-6.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-6.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-7.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-7.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-7.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-7.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>What he admired about the fledgling wheel diameter was the ability to adapt the <a href=\"https://wrensports.com/products/inverted-mtb-suspension-fork\" target=\"_blank\">Wren 150 mm travel fork</a> ($699!) to 120 mm of travel. “The fork is quite nice. Set and forget.”</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-18.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-18.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-18.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Stout-18.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>I was looking forward to seeing what Russell would bring this year, and it did not disappoint.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/stout_cycles/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\">@StoutCycles</a></h3>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-1.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://tomobikes.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\">Tomo Bikes Mid/Long Tail</a></h3>\n<p>Hot damn. “Where is the line drawn between mid and long tail? I don’t know,” stated Jonathan Thompson, who builds under the Tomo label. His work is that of experimentation. There were a few examples of “upcycling” at the 2026 Bespoked UK show this year, with the Tailfin/Albion bags, the Stayer CarryOn, and this stunning rigid MTB by Tomo Bikes.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-13.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-13.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-13.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-13.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-18.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-18.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-18.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-18.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>He explained that this bike began as a rigid 29er ten years ago, and last month he decided to chop the rear end off it and convert it to a mid/long-tail. “I just finished the bike this morning,” he said to me with a playful grin. Jonathan painted it himself, too, by the way.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-5.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-5.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-5.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-5.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-16.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-16.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-16.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-16.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-15.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-15.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-15.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-15.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>What I admire the most about the bike is not only the hand-brushed paint job, similar to the Zoceli we featured, but the fact that Jonathan kept the quick-release dropouts when making the conversion. “I’m very much fine with 11-speed drivetrains. Mechanical everything,” he said, lamenting the constant march towards new tech.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-17.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-17.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-17.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Tomo-17.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Tomo’s work is so fun and playful, and talking to Jonathan that afternoon was a real treat.</p>\n<p>Ride, safe, bud!</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/tomobikes/\" target=\"_blank\">@TomoBikes</a></h3>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-191.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-191.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-191.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-191.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-187.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-187.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-187.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-187.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-198.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-198.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-198.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-198.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><em><strong>We’ve got more on the way from the 2026 Bespoked UK in London!</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>Which build was your favorite? We’ve got a lot more on the way, so stay tuned…</strong></em></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/CoverageSponsoredby_Schwalbe_Brooks.png?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/CoverageSponsoredby_Schwalbe_Brooks.png?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/CoverageSponsoredby_Schwalbe_Brooks.png?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/CoverageSponsoredby_Schwalbe_Brooks.png?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><strong>The Radavist thanks <a href=\"https://www.brooksengland.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Brooks England</a> and <a href=\"https://www.schwalbe.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Schwalbe</a> for sponsoring our 2026 Bespoked UK coverage and our independent Reportage!</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h3>All of our 2026 Bespoked UK photos are in <a href=\"https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fo/ub22h6il3xptz4rylnp42/AEloQInROxd7SbFXSmyuPWw?rlkey=l5crjp8imc8scm6ufw7a478ug&amp;st=igwozq3p&amp;dl=0\" target=\"_blank\">The Radavist Dropbox</a> for builders to use.</h3>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/2026-bespoked-uk-03\">2026 Bespoked UK Selects 03: BabyLdn, Boyd Wheels, Julius Randonneur, Medusa, Quirk, Stout, Tomo</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://cms.theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"3bcc4d3d34324da12e76b9fc83ae18030d47736f61d4e540fd34eb5597a592f4","category":"Cycling"}